radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled and enlarged, measuring up to 11 mm in diameter, and with surrounding fat stranding, concerning for acute appendicitis. The visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal. No abnormalities in the gastrointestinal tract, pelvis, or retroperitoneal lymph nodes. No evidence of osseous lesions or acute fracture.
